A taxonomic study of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera, Mymaridae) from Heilongjiang, ChinaFive species of Ooctonus Haliday (Hymenoptera, Mymaridae) from Heilongjiang Province, China, are reviewed. One species, O. huberi sp. n., is described as new, and four species, O. orientalis Doutt, O. saturn Triapitsyn, O. sublaevis FÃ¶rster and O. vulgatus Haliday are reported as new to China. A key to the females of the 10 described Chinese species is given. All the specimens are deposited in the insect collections of Northeast Forestry University, China.